9%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%85%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to generalize, to extend the scope of","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to circulate, to disseminate, to publicize","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"أظنّ أنّ من المُستحسن ترجمة البيان إلى الإنجليزية وتعميمه على وكالات الأنباء العالمية.","english":"I reckon it advisable to translate the report to English and disseminate it to the global news agencies."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clothe with a turban (a person, their head)","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕam.ma.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30458","headword_ar":"عَمَمٌ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality, of being collected together, and numerous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Largeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bigness, of make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in men and in others. (K.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EumumN","text_ar":"عُمُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Complete,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without deficiency;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a body, and to a shoulder: (S:) or, applied to the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"long."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiymN","text_ar":"عَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  Applied to a beast of the bovine kind,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having all his teeth grown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) [See 8, last sentence; and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaDobN","text_ar":"عَضْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And Any affair, or event, or case,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complete"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplished"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and common"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"general"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universal"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commonly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generally"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"universally known"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b4-  And quasi. pl. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAm~apN","text_ar":"عَامَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. (K.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEam~N","text_ar":"مِعَمٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S"]},{"entry_id":"n30459","headword_ar":"عُمُمٌ","root":"Em","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Completeness of body"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bodily growth"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of wealth, and of youthful vigour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the period of youthfulness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisotawaY","text_ar":"اِسْتَوَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eumumihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عُمُمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) occurring in a trad. of 'Orweh Ibn-Ez-Zubeyr, on his mentioning Uheyhah Ibn-El-Juláh and the saying of his maternal uncles respecting him,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kun~aA A^ahola vum~ihi warum~ihi Hat~aY A@sotawaY","text_ar":"كُنَّا اَهْلَ ثُمِّهِ وَرُمِّهِ حَتَّى ا@سْتَوَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eumumihi","text_ar":"عَلَى عُمُمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We were the masters of the meaner and the better articles of his property until he attained to man's estate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to his completeness of bodily growth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (S;) [or] the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his completeness of stature and of bones and of limbs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) also pronounced with teshdeed [or idghám, i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eum~ihi","text_ar":"عُمِّهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"], for the sake of conformity [with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~ihi","text_ar":"ثُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rum~ihi","text_ar":"رُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, TA;) and by some, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eamamihi","text_ar":"عَمَمِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EamiymN","text_ar":"عَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}